    • Method Detail

      • addStep

        public PipelineBuilder<T> addStep(java.lang.String name,
                                  long attempts,
                                  kotlin.jvm.functions.Function2<? super T,? super kotlin.coroutines.experimental.Continuation<? super T>,? extends java.lang.Object> step)

        Adds a step in the pipeline.

        Parameters:
        name - A name for this step. This should ideally be unique, but it's not required. This will appear in the logs and any exception messages.
        attempts - The maximum number of attempts to be made in case this step throws an exception.
        step - A pure input-output function defining the business logic in the step. Note that we cannot prevent you from affecting any global state in the body of the step. However, that is almost always a bad idea. This function will be shared among the different jobs that will be push-started via this pipeline. Additionally, it may be invoked multiple times due to retries. Therefore, it's best to architect your pipeline such that they only use pure functional steps.

      • addCountedBarrier

        public PipelineBuilder<T> addCountedBarrier(java.lang.String name,
                                            int capacity,
                                            long attempts,
                                            kotlin.jvm.functions.Function2<? super java.util.List<? extends T>,? super kotlin.coroutines.experimental.Continuation<? super java.util.List<? extends T>>,? extends java.lang.Object> onBarrierLiftedAction)

        Adds a counted barrier in the pipeline. A handle to the corresponding interface CountedBarrierController can be retrieved once the pipeline is created via Pipeline.getCountedBarriers::get(i).

        Parameters:
        name - A name for this barrier. This should ideally be unique, but it's not required. This will appear in the logs and any exception messages.
        capacity - The initial capacity for this counted barrier.
        attempts - The maximum number of attempts to be made in case onBarrierLiftedAction throws an exception.
        onBarrierLiftedAction - An optional aggregation task that can be performed on the list of items received from the previous step.
        See Also:
        interface CountedBarrierController, Pipeline.getCountedBarriers
